article.headline: Texas Tech 84, Oklahoma 58
article.story: LUBBOCK, Texas -- Mike Singletary and David Tairu scored 17 points each to lead Texas Tech over Oklahoma 84-58 on Wednesday night, handing the Sooners their eighth straight loss. Wally Dunn added 15 points and Brad Reese had 12 for the Red Raiders (13-17, 5-10 Big 12), who hit 11 of 21 3-pointers and led the whole way -- much of it by double digits. Cade Davis scored 21 points to lead Oklahoma (12-17, 4-11), which shot just 32.8 percent from the field, hitting 21 of 64 shots. Texas Tech outrebounded Oklahoma 46-37 but had more turnovers, 16, than the Sooners' 12. But Oklahoma got just 11 points off the turnovers, while Texas Tech scored 21 points off Sooners' turnovers. The game got sloppy at times, leading to eight steals for each team.
